HEADWORD: Anomia
<hw>A*no"mi*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ irregular; <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <grk>no`mos</grk> law.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of bivalve shells, allied to the oyster,
so called from their unequal valves, of which the lower is perforated
for attachment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anomophyllous</ent>⟦br⟧
